ed to check if tests can run, and I'm wondering about the potential issue of the native image not being able to load non-public classes. Our inner class is public static, but its binary name includes a `$`, which raises questions about naming rules.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Identifying testing challenges**\\\\n\\\\nI’m noticing a potential issue with only adding tests without metadata. I wonder if imports in the build are necessary, but it seems I don’t need to worry about that. My main concern is with JUnit possibly running tests in an arbitrary order. This could lead to issues with the static methodCache, especially if another test deserializes the same class before my custom test. I'm curious if the dynamic call site coverage from the JVM run factors into this as well.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Checking class loading issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether a potential issue arises if `roundTripsCustomLevel...` gets repeated after the first call. There's a chance that methodCache could skip `getDeclaredMethod`, but the dynamic coverage gathered so far indicates that it sees the initial one. It’s crucial to think about whether the test’s custom class `SerializableLevel` is initialized directly before `Loader.loadClass`. I wonder if `Loader.loadClass` recognizes the already-loaded Class through TCCL. I should inspect the Loader further.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_p1xKiEbKkYReKuun8GkpNfto|fc_09b857ba06023e1f0169f502f170108192b0229c0733220826\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/helpers/Loader.java\", \"offset\": 130, \"limit\": 90}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 858, \"output\": 1722, \"cacheRead\": 24576, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"to